STATE OF OREGON, Respondent, v. WIMPY DEWEY JONES, Appellant. (No. 73582) 494 P2d 903 F. E. Glenn, Deputy Public Defender, Salem, argued tbe cause for appellant. With Mm on the brief was Gary D. Babcock, Public Defender, Salem. Gary D. Gortmaher, District Attorney, Salem, argued the cause and filed the brief for respondent.

Argued March 28,

affirmed March 28,

petition for rehearing denied April 25, petition for review denied May 31, 1972

Before Schwab, Chief Judge, and Foley and Fort, Judges.
